dcterms:description: A dataset containing all possible graphs of size 7 and less, where the nodes can be one of two colors. It allows for the computation of the true distribution p(x) and the learned p(x; θ) for x ∈ X relatively quickly.
dcterms:title: Graphs of size 7 and less

dcterms:description: A hypergrid environment used for evaluating GFlowNets, where the agent navigates on a grid of size M (64 in experiments) and is forced to stop if any of the coordinates reaches M - 1.
dcterms:title: Hypergrid environment

dcterms:description: A sequence environment used in GFlowNet literature, where the reward is based on the Levenshtein edit distance between an input sequence and the closest mode sequence.
dcterms:title: Sequence environment
